  // Wait, does our Zod schema validate password matching?
  // Yes, but let's make sure. If the Zod schema is refined, the fieldErrors might contain root errors.
  // Wait, let's look at how we can refine. Can we refine the schema inside zod$?
  // Yes! Let's check: in Zod, z.object({ ... }).refine(...) is a valid schema.
  // Wait, does Qwik City's zod$ support refined object schema? Yes, completely, because a refined schema is a ZodType.
  // Wait, let's refine the schema to check if password matches confirmPassword.
  // Let's modify our zod$ schema to include the password match refine!
  return (
    <div class="container">
      <div class="wizard-header">
        <h1 class="wizard-title">Create Account</h1>
        <p class="wizard-subtitle">Step 1 of 3 — Account details</p>
      </div>

      {/* Progress Indicator */}
      <div class="progress-steps">
        <div class="step-item active">
          <div class="step-circle">1</div>
          <div class="step-label">Account</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-circle">2</div>
          <div class="step-label">Profile</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-circle">3</div>
          <div class="step-label">Review</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="form-card">
        <Form action={action} novalidate>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label class="form-label" for="email">
              Email Address
            </label>
            <input
              type="email"
              id="email"
              name="email"
              value={emailValue}
              class={`form-input ${action.value?.fieldErrors?.email ? "has-error" : ""}`}
              placeholder="you@example.com"
            />
            {action.value?.fieldErrors?.email && (
              <p class="error-message">{action.value.fieldErrors.email[0]}</p>
            )}
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <label class="form-label" for="password">
              Password
            </label>
            <input
              type="password"
              id="password"
              name="password"
              value={passwordValue}
              class={`form-input ${action.value?.fieldErrors?.password ? "has-error" : ""}`}
              placeholder="••••••••"
            />
            {action.value?.fieldErrors?.password && (
              <p class="error-message">{action.value.fieldErrors.password[0]}</p>
            )}
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <label class="form-label" for="confirmPassword">
              Confirm Password
            </label>
            <input
              type="password"
              id="confirmPassword"
